[div class=p 
	"In terms of entertainment, fighting games can be rather dull to TAS since the fastest way to beat the enemy sometimes happens to be very straight forward and repetitive. That's why playaround / glitch demonstrations can be more favourable when it comes to these games. In this case, fatalities are the most sorely missed element, being a central aspect of what makes Mortal Kombat such an appealing game.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"None of the above precludes acceptability. We're in the business of beating games fast and this movie certainly does it, and in an evidently optimized fashion. Furthermore, the fights here are satisfingly violent and fast-paced. The use of damage amplifiers make quick rid of the enemies at the expense of some health (takes damage to go faster). Finally, the final boss is indeed fatalized (fastest way to end the game).
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Accepting to Standard
	$LF
